8 // ----
9 // This file implements a function pass that inserts VSETVLI instructions where ----
10 // needed and expands the vl outputs of VLEFF/VLSEGFF to PseudoReadVL ----
11 // instructions. ----
12 // ----
13 // This pass consists of 3 phases: ----
14 // ----
15 // Phase 1 collects how each basic block affects VL/VTYPE. ----
16 // ----
17 // Phase 2 uses the information from phase 1 to do a data flow analysis to ----
18 // propagate the VL/VTYPE changes through the function. This gives us the ----
19 // VL/VTYPE at the start of each basic block. ----
20 // ----
21 // Phase 3 inserts VSETVLI instructions in each basic block. Information from ----
22 // phase 2 is used to prevent inserting a VSETVLI before the first vector ----
23 // instruction in the block if possible. ----
24 // ----
25 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
26 ----

142 static bool isMaskRegOp(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
143 if (!RISCVII::hasSEWOp(MI.getDesc().TSFlags)) 0
144 return false; 0
145 const unsigned Log2SEW = MI.getOperand(getSEWOpNum(MI)).getImm(); 0
146 // A Log2SEW of 0 is an operation on mask registers only. ----
147 return Log2SEW == 0; 0
148 } ----

150 /// Return true if the inactive elements in the result are entirely undefined. ----
151 /// Note that this is different from "agnostic" as defined by the vector ----
152 /// specification. Agnostic requires each lane to either be undisturbed, or ----
153 /// take the value -1; no other value is allowed. ----
154 static bool hasUndefinedMergeOp(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
155 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
156 ----
157 unsigned UseOpIdx; ----
158 if (!MI.isRegTiedToUseOperand(0, &UseOpIdx)) 0
159 // If there is no passthrough operand, then the pass through ----
160 // lanes are undefined. ----
161 return true; 0
162 ----
163 // If the tied operand is an IMPLICIT_DEF (or a REG_SEQUENCE whose operands ----
164 // are solely IMPLICIT_DEFS), the pass through lanes are undefined. ----
165 const MachineOperand &UseMO = MI.getOperand(UseOpIdx); 0
166 if (MachineInstr *UseMI = MRI.getVRegDef(UseMO.getReg())) { 0
167 if (UseMI->isImplicitDef()) 0
168 return true; 0
169 ----
170 if (UseMI->isRegSequence()) { 0
171 for (unsigned i = 1, e = UseMI->getNumOperands(); i < e; i += 2) { 0
172 MachineInstr *SourceMI = MRI.getVRegDef(UseMI->getOperand(i).getReg()); 0
173 if (!SourceMI || !SourceMI->isImplicitDef()) 0
174 return false; 0
175 } ----
176 return true; 0
177 } ----
178 } ----
179 return false; 0
180 } ----

182 /// Which subfields of VL or VTYPE have values we need to preserve? ----
183 struct DemandedFields { ----
184 // Some unknown property of VL is used. If demanded, must preserve entire ----
185 // value. ----
186 bool VLAny = false; ----
187 // Only zero vs non-zero is used. If demanded, can change non-zero values. ----
188 bool VLZeroness = false; ----
189 // What properties of SEW we need to preserve. ----
190 enum : uint8_t { ----
191 SEWEqual = 2, // The exact value of SEW needs to be preserved. ----
192 SEWGreaterThanOrEqual = 1, // SEW can be changed as long as it's greater ----
193 // than or equal to the original value. ----
194 SEWNone = 0 // We don't need to preserve SEW at all. ----
195 } SEW = SEWNone; ----
196 bool LMUL = false; ----
197 bool SEWLMULRatio = false; ----
198 bool TailPolicy = false; ----
199 bool MaskPolicy = false; ----
200 ----
201 // Return true if any part of VTYPE was used ----
202 bool usedVTYPE() const { 0
203 return SEW || LMUL || SEWLMULRatio || TailPolicy || MaskPolicy; 0
204 } ----
205 ----
206 // Return true if any property of VL was used ----
207 bool usedVL() { 0
208 return VLAny || VLZeroness; 0
209 } ----
210 ----
211 // Mark all VTYPE subfields and properties as demanded ----
212 void demandVTYPE() { 0
213 SEW = SEWEqual; 0
214 LMUL = true; 0
215 SEWLMULRatio = true; 0
216 TailPolicy = true; 0
217 MaskPolicy = true; 0
218 } 0
219 ----
220 // Mark all VL properties as demanded ----
221 void demandVL() { 0
222 VLAny = true; 0
223 VLZeroness = true; 0
224 } 0

268 /// Return true if moving from CurVType to NewVType is ----
269 /// indistinguishable from the perspective of an instruction (or set ----
270 /// of instructions) which use only the Used subfields and properties. ----
271 static bool areCompatibleVTYPEs(uint64_t CurVType, uint64_t NewVType, 0
272 const DemandedFields &Used) { ----
273 if (Used.SEW == DemandedFields::SEWEqual && 0
274 RISCVVType::getSEW(CurVType) != RISCVVType::getSEW(NewVType)) 0
275 return false; 0
276 ----
277 if (Used.SEW == DemandedFields::SEWGreaterThanOrEqual && 0
278 RISCVVType::getSEW(NewVType) < RISCVVType::getSEW(CurVType)) 0
279 return false; 0
280 ----
281 if (Used.LMUL && 0
282 RISCVVType::getVLMUL(CurVType) != RISCVVType::getVLMUL(NewVType)) 0
283 return false; 0
284 ----
285 if (Used.SEWLMULRatio) { 0
286 auto Ratio1 = RISCVVType::getSEWLMULRatio(RISCVVType::getSEW(CurVType), 0
287 RISCVVType::getVLMUL(CurVType)); 0
288 auto Ratio2 = RISCVVType::getSEWLMULRatio(RISCVVType::getSEW(NewVType), 0
289 RISCVVType::getVLMUL(NewVType)); 0
290 if (Ratio1 != Ratio2) 0
291 return false; 0
292 } ----
293 ----
294 if (Used.TailPolicy && RISCVVType::isTailAgnostic(CurVType) != 0
295 RISCVVType::isTailAgnostic(NewVType)) 0
296 return false; 0
297 if (Used.MaskPolicy && RISCVVType::isMaskAgnostic(CurVType) != 0
298 RISCVVType::isMaskAgnostic(NewVType)) 0
299 return false; 0
300 return true; 0
301 } ----

303 /// Return the fields and properties demanded by the provided instruction. ----
304 DemandedFields getDemanded(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
305 const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI) { ----
306 // Warning: This function has to work on both the lowered (i.e. post ----
307 // emitVSETVLIs) and pre-lowering forms. The main implication of this is ----
308 // that it can't use the value of a SEW, VL, or Policy operand as they might ----
309 // be stale after lowering. ----
310 ----
311 // Most instructions don't use any of these subfeilds. ----
312 DemandedFields Res; 0
313 // Start conservative if registers are used ----
314 if (MI.isCall() || MI.isInlineAsm() || MI.readsRegister(RISCV::VL)) 0
315 Res.demandVL(); 0
316 if (MI.isCall() || MI.isInlineAsm() || MI.readsRegister(RISCV::VTYPE)) 0
317 Res.demandVTYPE(); 0
318 // Start conservative on the unlowered form too ----
319 uint64_t TSFlags = MI.getDesc().TSFlags; 0
320 if (RISCVII::hasSEWOp(TSFlags)) { 0
321 Res.demandVTYPE(); 0
322 if (RISCVII::hasVLOp(TSFlags)) 0
323 Res.demandVL(); 0
324 ----
325 // Behavior is independent of mask policy. ----
326 if (!RISCVII::usesMaskPolicy(TSFlags)) 0
327 Res.MaskPolicy = false; 0
328 } ----
329 ----
330 // Loads and stores with implicit EEW do not demand SEW or LMUL directly. ----
331 // They instead demand the ratio of the two which is used in computing ----
332 // EMUL, but which allows us the flexibility to change SEW and LMUL ----
333 // provided we don't change the ratio. ----
334 // Note: We assume that the instructions initial SEW is the EEW encoded ----
335 // in the opcode. This is asserted when constructing the VSETVLIInfo. ----
336 if (getEEWForLoadStore(MI)) { 0
337 Res.SEW = DemandedFields::SEWNone; 0
338 Res.LMUL = false; 0
339 } ----
340 ----
341 // Store instructions don't use the policy fields. ----
342 if (RISCVII::hasSEWOp(TSFlags) && MI.getNumExplicitDefs() == 0) { 0
343 Res.TailPolicy = false; 0
344 Res.MaskPolicy = false; 0
345 } ----
346 ----
347 // If this is a mask reg operation, it only cares about VLMAX. ----
348 // TODO: Possible extensions to this logic ----
349 // * Probably ok if available VLMax is larger than demanded ----
350 // * The policy bits can probably be ignored.. ----
351 if (isMaskRegOp(MI)) { 0
352 Res.SEW = DemandedFields::SEWNone; 0
353 Res.LMUL = false; 0
354 } ----
355 ----
356 // For vmv.s.x and vfmv.s.f, there are only two behaviors, VL = 0 and VL > 0. ----
357 if (isScalarMoveInstr(MI)) { 0
358 Res.LMUL = false; 0
359 Res.SEWLMULRatio = false; 0
360 Res.VLAny = false; 0
361 // For vmv.s.x and vfmv.s.f, if the merge operand is *undefined*, we don't ----
362 // need to preserve any other bits and are thus compatible with any larger, ----
363 // etype and can disregard policy bits. Warning: It's tempting to try doing ----
364 // this for any tail agnostic operation, but we can't as TA requires ----
365 // tail lanes to either be the original value or -1. We are writing ----
366 // unknown bits to the lanes here. ----
367 if (hasUndefinedMergeOp(MI, *MRI)) { 0
368 Res.SEW = DemandedFields::SEWGreaterThanOrEqual; 0
369 Res.TailPolicy = false; 0
370 } ----
371 } ----
372 ----
373 return Res; 0
374 } ----

376 /// Defines the abstract state with which the forward dataflow models the ----
377 /// values of the VL and VTYPE registers after insertion. ----
378 class VSETVLIInfo { ----
379 union { ----
380 Register AVLReg; ----
381 unsigned AVLImm; ----
382 }; ----
383 ----
384 enum : uint8_t { ----
385 Uninitialized, ----
386 AVLIsReg, ----
387 AVLIsImm, ----
388 Unknown, ----
389 } State = Uninitialized; ----
390 ----
391 // Fields from VTYPE. ----
392 RISCVII::VLMUL VLMul = RISCVII::LMUL_1; ----
393 uint8_t SEW = 0; ----
394 uint8_t TailAgnostic : 1; ----
395 uint8_t MaskAgnostic : 1; ----
396 uint8_t SEWLMULRatioOnly : 1; ----
397 ----
398 public: ----
399 VSETVLIInfo() 0
400 : AVLImm(0), TailAgnostic(false), MaskAgnostic(false), 0
401 SEWLMULRatioOnly(false) {} 0
402 ----
403 static VSETVLIInfo getUnknown() { 0
404 VSETVLIInfo Info; 0
405 Info.setUnknown(); 0
406 return Info; 0
407 } ----
408 ----
409 bool isValid() const { return State != Uninitialized; } 0
410 void setUnknown() { State = Unknown; } 0
411 bool isUnknown() const { return State == Unknown; } 0
412 ----
413 void setAVLReg(Register Reg) { 0
414 AVLReg = Reg; 0
415 State = AVLIsReg; 0
416 } 0
417 ----
418 void setAVLImm(unsigned Imm) { 0
419 AVLImm = Imm; 0
420 State = AVLIsImm; 0
421 } 0
422 ----
423 bool hasAVLImm() const { return State == AVLIsImm; } 0
424 bool hasAVLReg() const { return State == AVLIsReg; } 0

426 assert(hasAVLReg()); 0
427 return AVLReg; 0
428 } ----

437 bool hasNonZeroAVL(const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) const { 0
438 if (hasAVLImm()) 0
439 return getAVLImm() > 0; 0
440 if (hasAVLReg()) { 0
441 if (getAVLReg() == RISCV::X0) 0
442 return true; 0

444 MI && MI->getOpcode() == RISCV::ADDI && 0

446 MI->getOperand(1).getReg() == RISCV::X0 && 0
447 MI->getOperand(2).getImm() != 0) 0
448 return true; 0
449 return false; 0
450 } ----
451 return false; 0
452 } ----

514 // Check if the VTYPE for these two VSETVLIInfos produce the same VLMAX. ----
515 // Note that having the same VLMAX ensures that both share the same ----
516 // function from AVL to VL; that is, they must produce the same VL value ----
517 // for any given AVL value. ----
518 bool hasSameVLMAX(const VSETVLIInfo &Other) const { 0
519 assert(isValid() && Other.isValid() && 0
520 "Can't compare invalid VSETVLIInfos"); ----
521 assert(!isUnknown() && !Other.isUnknown() && 0
522 "Can't compare VTYPE in unknown state"); ----
523 return getSEWLMULRatio() == Other.getSEWLMULRatio(); 0
524 } ----

531 // Determine whether the vector instructions requirements represented by ----
532 // Require are compatible with the previous vsetvli instruction represented ----
533 // by this. MI is the instruction whose requirements we're considering. ----
534 bool isCompatible(const DemandedFields &Used, const VSETVLIInfo &Require, 0
535 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) const { ----
536 assert(isValid() && Require.isValid() && 0
537 "Can't compare invalid VSETVLIInfos"); ----
538 assert(!Require.SEWLMULRatioOnly && 0
539 "Expected a valid VTYPE for instruction!"); ----
540 // Nothing is compatible with Unknown. ----
541 if (isUnknown() || Require.isUnknown()) 0
542 return false; 0
543 ----
544 // If only our VLMAX ratio is valid, then this isn't compatible. ----
545 if (SEWLMULRatioOnly) 0
546 return false; 0
547 ----
548 // If the instruction doesn't need an AVLReg and the SEW matches, consider ----
549 // it compatible. ----
550 if (Require.hasAVLReg() && Require.AVLReg == RISCV::NoRegister) 0
551 if (SEW == Require.SEW) 0
552 return true; 0
553 ----
554 if (Used.VLAny && !hasSameAVL(Require)) 0
555 return false; 0
556 ----
557 if (Used.VLZeroness && !hasEquallyZeroAVL(Require, MRI)) 0
558 return false; 0
559 ----
560 return hasCompatibleVTYPE(Used, Require); 0
561 } ----
562 ----
563 bool operator==(const VSETVLIInfo &Other) const { 0
564 // Uninitialized is only equal to another Uninitialized. ----
565 if (!isValid()) 0
566 return !Other.isValid(); 0
567 if (!Other.isValid()) 0
568 return !isValid(); 0
569 ----
570 // Unknown is only equal to another Unknown. ----
571 if (isUnknown()) 0
572 return Other.isUnknown(); 0
573 if (Other.isUnknown()) 0
574 return isUnknown(); 0
575 ----
576 if (!hasSameAVL(Other)) 0
577 return false; 0
578 ----
579 // If the SEWLMULRatioOnly bits are different, then they aren't equal. ----
580 if (SEWLMULRatioOnly != Other.SEWLMULRatioOnly) 0
581 return false; 0
582 ----
583 // If only the VLMAX is valid, check that it is the same. ----
584 if (SEWLMULRatioOnly) 0
585 return hasSameVLMAX(Other); 0
586 ----
587 // If the full VTYPE is valid, check that it is the same. ----
588 return hasSameVTYPE(Other); 0
589 } ----
590 ----
591 bool operator!=(const VSETVLIInfo &Other) const { 0
592 return !(*this == Other); 0
593 } ----

595 // Calculate the VSETVLIInfo visible to a block assuming this and Other are ----
596 // both predecessors. ----
597 VSETVLIInfo intersect(const VSETVLIInfo &Other) const { 0
598 // If the new value isn't valid, ignore it. ----
599 if (!Other.isValid()) 0
600 return *this; 0
601 ----
602 // If this value isn't valid, this must be the first predecessor, use it. ----
603 if (!isValid()) 0
604 return Other; 0
605 ----
606 // If either is unknown, the result is unknown. ----
607 if (isUnknown() || Other.isUnknown()) 0
608 return VSETVLIInfo::getUnknown(); 0
609 ----
610 // If we have an exact, match return this. ----
611 if (*this == Other) 0
612 return *this; 0
613 ----
614 // Not an exact match, but maybe the AVL and VLMAX are the same. If so, ----
615 // return an SEW/LMUL ratio only value. ----
616 if (hasSameAVL(Other) && hasSameVLMAX(Other)) { 0
617 VSETVLIInfo MergeInfo = *this; 0
618 MergeInfo.SEWLMULRatioOnly = true; 0
619 return MergeInfo; 0
620 } ----
621 ----
622 // Otherwise the result is unknown. ----
623 return VSETVLIInfo::getUnknown(); 0
624 } ----
625 ----
626 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
627 /// Support for debugging, callable in GDB: V->dump() ----
628 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void dump() const { 0
629 print(dbgs()); 0
630 dbgs() << "\n"; 0
631 } 0
632 ----
633 /// Implement operator<<. ----
634 /// @{ ----
635 void print(raw_ostream &OS) const { 0
636 OS << "{"; 0
637 if (!isValid()) 0
638 OS << "Uninitialized"; 0
639 if (isUnknown()) 0
640 OS << "unknown"; 0
641 if (hasAVLReg()) 0
642 OS << "AVLReg=" << (unsigned)AVLReg; 0
643 if (hasAVLImm()) 0
644 OS << "AVLImm=" << (unsigned)AVLImm; 0
645 OS << ", " 0
646 << "VLMul=" << (unsigned)VLMul << ", " 0
647 << "SEW=" << (unsigned)SEW << ", " 0
648 << "TailAgnostic=" << (bool)TailAgnostic << ", " 0
649 << "MaskAgnostic=" << (bool)MaskAgnostic << ", " 0
650 << "SEWLMULRatioOnly=" << (bool)SEWLMULRatioOnly << "}"; 0
651 } 0
652 #endif ----
653 }; ----
654 ----
655 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
656 LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_USED ----
657 inline raw_ostream &operator<<(raw_ostream &OS, const VSETVLIInfo &V) { 0
658 V.print(OS); 0
659 return OS; 0
660 } ----

662 ----
663 struct BlockData { ----
664 // The VSETVLIInfo that represents the net changes to the VL/VTYPE registers ----
665 // made by this block. Calculated in Phase 1. ----
666 VSETVLIInfo Change; ----
667 ----
668 // The VSETVLIInfo that represents the VL/VTYPE settings on exit from this ----
669 // block. Calculated in Phase 2. ----
670 VSETVLIInfo Exit; ----
671 ----
672 // The VSETVLIInfo that represents the VL/VTYPE settings from all predecessor ----
673 // blocks. Calculated in Phase 2, and used by Phase 3. ----
674 VSETVLIInfo Pred; ----
675 ----
676 // Keeps track of whether the block is already in the queue. ----
677 bool InQueue = false; ----
678 ----
679 BlockData() = default; 0
680 }; ----

728 ----
729 INITIALIZE_PASS(RISCVInsertVSETVLI, DEBUG_TYPE, RISCV_INSERT_VSETVLI_NAME, 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
730 false, false) ----
731 ----
732 static VSETVLIInfo computeInfoForInstr(const MachineInstr &MI, uint64_t TSFlags, 0
733 const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI) { ----
734 VSETVLIInfo InstrInfo; 0
735 ----
736 bool TailAgnostic = true; 0
737 bool MaskAgnostic = true; 0
738 if (!hasUndefinedMergeOp(MI, *MRI)) { 0
739 // Start with undisturbed. ----
740 TailAgnostic = false; 0
741 MaskAgnostic = false; 0
742 ----
743 // If there is a policy operand, use it. ----
744 if (RISCVII::hasVecPolicyOp(TSFlags)) { 0
745 const MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(MI.getNumExplicitOperands() - 1); 0
746 uint64_t Policy = Op.getImm(); 0
747 assert(Policy <= (RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC | RISCVII::MASK_AGNOSTIC) && 0
748 "Invalid Policy Value"); ----
749 TailAgnostic = Policy & RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC; 0
750 MaskAgnostic = Policy & RISCVII::MASK_AGNOSTIC; 0
751 } ----
752 ----
753 // Some pseudo instructions force a tail agnostic policy despite having a ----
754 // tied def. ----
755 if (RISCVII::doesForceTailAgnostic(TSFlags)) 0
756 TailAgnostic = true; 0
757 ----
758 if (!RISCVII::usesMaskPolicy(TSFlags)) 0
759 MaskAgnostic = true; 0
760 } ----
761 ----
762 RISCVII::VLMUL VLMul = RISCVII::getLMul(TSFlags); 0
763 ----
764 unsigned Log2SEW = MI.getOperand(getSEWOpNum(MI)).getImm(); 0
765 // A Log2SEW of 0 is an operation on mask registers only. ----
766 unsigned SEW = Log2SEW ? 1 << Log2SEW : 8; 0
767 assert(RISCVVType::isValidSEW(SEW) && "Unexpected SEW"); 0
768 ----
769 if (RISCVII::hasVLOp(TSFlags)) { 0
770 const MachineOperand &VLOp = MI.getOperand(getVLOpNum(MI)); 0
771 if (VLOp.isImm()) { 0
772 int64_t Imm = VLOp.getImm(); 0
773 // Conver the VLMax sentintel to X0 register. ----
774 if (Imm == RISCV::VLMaxSentinel) 0
775 InstrInfo.setAVLReg(RISCV::X0); 0
776 else ----
777 InstrInfo.setAVLImm(Imm); 0
778 } else { ----
779 InstrInfo.setAVLReg(VLOp.getReg()); 0
780 } ----
781 } else { ----
782 InstrInfo.setAVLReg(RISCV::NoRegister); 0
783 } ----
784 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
785 if (std::optional EEW = getEEWForLoadStore(MI)) { 0
786 assert(SEW == EEW && "Initial SEW doesn't match expected EEW"); 0
787 } ----
788 #endif ----
789 InstrInfo.setVTYPE(VLMul, SEW, TailAgnostic, MaskAgnostic); 0
790 ----
791 return InstrInfo; 0
792 } ----
793 ----
794 void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::insertVSETVLI(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineInstr &MI, 0
795 const VSETVLIInfo &Info, ----
796 const VSETVLIInfo &PrevInfo) { ----
797 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
798 insertVSETVLI(MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator(&MI), DL, Info, PrevInfo); 0
799 } 0
800 ----
801 // Return a VSETVLIInfo representing the changes made by this VSETVLI or ----
802 // VSETIVLI instruction. ----
803 static VSETVLIInfo getInfoForVSETVLI(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
804 VSETVLIInfo NewInfo; 0
805 if (MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::PseudoVSETIVLI) { 0
806 NewInfo.setAVLImm(MI.getOperand(1).getImm()); 0
807 } else { ----
808 assert(MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::PseudoVSETVLI || 0
809 MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::PseudoVSETVLIX0); ----
810 Register AVLReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
811 assert((AVLReg != RISCV::X0 || MI.getOperand(0).getReg() != RISCV::X0) && 0
812 "Can't handle X0, X0 vsetvli yet"); ----
813 NewInfo.setAVLReg(AVLReg); 0
814 } ----
815 NewInfo.setVTYPE(MI.getOperand(2).getImm()); 0
816 ----
817 return NewInfo; 0
818 } ----
819 ----
820 void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::insertVSETVLI(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
821 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPt, DebugLoc DL, ----
822 const VSETVLIInfo &Info, const VSETVLIInfo &PrevInfo) { ----
823 ----
824 if (PrevInfo.isValid() && !PrevInfo.isUnknown()) { 0
825 // Use X0, X0 form if the AVL is the same and the SEW+LMUL gives the same ----
826 // VLMAX. ----
827 if (Info.hasSameAVL(PrevInfo) && Info.hasSameVLMAX(PrevInfo)) { 0
828 BuildMI(MBB, InsertPt, DL, TII->get(RISCV::PseudoVSETVLIX0)) 0
829 .addReg(RISCV::X0, RegState::Define | RegState::Dead) 0
830 .addReg(RISCV::X0, RegState::Kill) 0
831 .addImm(Info.encodeVTYPE()) 0
832 .addReg(RISCV::VL, RegState::Implicit); 0
833 return; 0
834 } ----
835 ----
836 // If our AVL is a virtual register, it might be defined by a VSET(I)VLI. If ----
837 // it has the same VLMAX we want and the last VL/VTYPE we observed is the ----
838 // same, we can use the X0, X0 form. ----
839 if (Info.hasSameVLMAX(PrevInfo) && Info.hasAVLReg() && 0
840 Info.getAVLReg().isVirtual()) { 0
841 if (MachineInstr *DefMI = MRI->getVRegDef(Info.getAVLReg())) { 0
842 if (isVectorConfigInstr(*DefMI)) { 0
843 VSETVLIInfo DefInfo = getInfoForVSETVLI(*DefMI); 0
844 if (DefInfo.hasSameAVL(PrevInfo) && DefInfo.hasSameVLMAX(PrevInfo)) { 0
845 BuildMI(MBB, InsertPt, DL, TII->get(RISCV::PseudoVSETVLIX0)) 0
846 .addReg(RISCV::X0, RegState::Define | RegState::Dead) 0
847 .addReg(RISCV::X0, RegState::Kill) 0
848 .addImm(Info.encodeVTYPE()) 0
849 .addReg(RISCV::VL, RegState::Implicit); 0
850 return; 0
851 } ----
852 } ----
853 } ----
854 } ----
855 } ----
856 ----
857 if (Info.hasAVLImm()) { 0
858 BuildMI(MBB, InsertPt, DL, TII->get(RISCV::PseudoVSETIVLI)) 0
859 .addReg(RISCV::X0, RegState::Define | RegState::Dead) 0
860 .addImm(Info.getAVLImm()) 0
861 .addImm(Info.encodeVTYPE()); 0
862 return; 0
863 } ----
864 ----
865 Register AVLReg = Info.getAVLReg(); 0
866 if (AVLReg == RISCV::NoRegister) { 0
867 // We can only use x0, x0 if there's no chance of the vtype change causing ----
868 // the previous vl to become invalid. ----
869 if (PrevInfo.isValid() && !PrevInfo.isUnknown() && 0
870 Info.hasSameVLMAX(PrevInfo)) { 0
871 BuildMI(MBB, InsertPt, DL, TII->get(RISCV::PseudoVSETVLIX0)) 0
872 .addReg(RISCV::X0, RegState::Define | RegState::Dead) 0
873 .addReg(RISCV::X0, RegState::Kill) 0
874 .addImm(Info.encodeVTYPE()) 0
875 .addReg(RISCV::VL, RegState::Implicit); 0
876 return; 0
877 } ----
878 // Otherwise use an AVL of 0 to avoid depending on previous vl. ----
879 BuildMI(MBB, InsertPt, DL, TII->get(RISCV::PseudoVSETIVLI)) 0
880 .addReg(RISCV::X0, RegState::Define | RegState::Dead) 0
881 .addImm(0) 0
882 .addImm(Info.encodeVTYPE()); 0
883 return; 0
884 } ----
885 ----
886 if (AVLReg.isVirtual()) 0
887 MRI->constrainRegClass(AVLReg, &RISCV::GPRNoX0RegClass); 0
888 ----
889 // Use X0 as the DestReg unless AVLReg is X0. We also need to change the ----
890 // opcode if the AVLReg is X0 as they have different register classes for ----
891 // the AVL operand. ----
892 Register DestReg = RISCV::X0; 0
893 unsigned Opcode = RISCV::PseudoVSETVLI; 0
894 if (AVLReg == RISCV::X0) { 0
895 DestReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&RISCV::GPRRegClass); 0
896 Opcode = RISCV::PseudoVSETVLIX0; 0
897 } ----
898 BuildMI(MBB, InsertPt, DL, TII->get(Opcode)) 0
899 .addReg(DestReg, RegState::Define | RegState::Dead) 0
900 .addReg(AVLReg) 0
901 .addImm(Info.encodeVTYPE()); 0
902 } ----
903 ----
904 static bool isLMUL1OrSmaller(RISCVII::VLMUL LMUL) { 0
905 auto [LMul, Fractional] = RISCVVType::decodeVLMUL(LMUL); 0
906 return Fractional || LMul == 1; 0
907 } ----
908 ----
909 /// Return true if a VSETVLI is required to transition from CurInfo to Require ----
910 /// before MI. ----
911 bool RISCVInsertVSETVLI::needVSETVLI(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
912 const VSETVLIInfo &Require, ----
913 const VSETVLIInfo &CurInfo) const { ----
914 assert(Require == computeInfoForInstr(MI, MI.getDesc().TSFlags, MRI)); 0
915 ----
916 if (!CurInfo.isValid() || CurInfo.isUnknown() || CurInfo.hasSEWLMULRatioOnly()) 0
917 return true; 0
918 ----
919 DemandedFields Used = getDemanded(MI, MRI); 0
920 ----
921 // A slidedown/slideup with an *undefined* merge op can freely clobber ----
922 // elements not copied from the source vector (e.g. masked off, tail, or ----
923 // slideup's prefix). Notes: ----
924 // * We can't modify SEW here since the slide amount is in units of SEW. ----
925 // * VL=1 is special only because we have existing support for zero vs ----
926 // non-zero VL. We could generalize this if we had a VL > C predicate. ----
927 // * The LMUL1 restriction is for machines whose latency may depend on VL. ----
928 // * As above, this is only legal for tail "undefined" not "agnostic". ----
929 if (isVSlideInstr(MI) && Require.hasAVLImm() && Require.getAVLImm() == 1 && 0
930 isLMUL1OrSmaller(CurInfo.getVLMUL()) && hasUndefinedMergeOp(MI, *MRI)) { 0
931 Used.VLAny = false; 0
932 Used.VLZeroness = true; 0
933 Used.LMUL = false; 0
934 Used.TailPolicy = false; 0
935 } ----
936 ----
937 // A tail undefined vmv.v.i/x or vfmv.v.f with VL=1 can be treated in the same ----
938 // semantically as vmv.s.x. This is particularly useful since we don't have an ----
939 // immediate form of vmv.s.x, and thus frequently use vmv.v.i in it's place. ----
940 // Since a splat is non-constant time in LMUL, we do need to be careful to not ----
941 // increase the number of active vector registers (unlike for vmv.s.x.) ----
942 if (isScalarSplatInstr(MI) && Require.hasAVLImm() && Require.getAVLImm() == 1 && 0
943 isLMUL1OrSmaller(CurInfo.getVLMUL()) && hasUndefinedMergeOp(MI, *MRI)) { 0
944 Used.LMUL = false; 0
945 Used.SEWLMULRatio = false; 0
946 Used.VLAny = false; 0
947 Used.SEW = DemandedFields::SEWGreaterThanOrEqual; 0
948 Used.TailPolicy = false; 0
949 } ----
950 ----
951 if (CurInfo.isCompatible(Used, Require, *MRI)) 0
952 return false; 0
953 ----
954 // We didn't find a compatible value. If our AVL is a virtual register, ----
955 // it might be defined by a VSET(I)VLI. If it has the same VLMAX we need ----
956 // and the last VL/VTYPE we observed is the same, we don't need a ----
957 // VSETVLI here. ----
958 if (Require.hasAVLReg() && Require.getAVLReg().isVirtual() && 0
959 CurInfo.hasCompatibleVTYPE(Used, Require)) { 0
960 if (MachineInstr *DefMI = MRI->getVRegDef(Require.getAVLReg())) { 0
961 if (isVectorConfigInstr(*DefMI)) { 0
962 VSETVLIInfo DefInfo = getInfoForVSETVLI(*DefMI); 0
963 if (DefInfo.hasSameAVL(CurInfo) && DefInfo.hasSameVLMAX(CurInfo)) 0
964 return false; 0
965 } ----
966 } ----
967 } ----
968 ----
969 return true; 0
970 } ----
971 ----
972 // Given an incoming state reaching MI, modifies that state so that it is minimally ----
973 // compatible with MI. The resulting state is guaranteed to be semantically legal ----
974 // for MI, but may not be the state requested by MI. ----
975 void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::transferBefore(VSETVLIInfo &Info, const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
976 uint64_t TSFlags = MI.getDesc().TSFlags; 0
977 if (!RISCVII::hasSEWOp(TSFlags)) 0
978 return; 0
979 ----
980 const VSETVLIInfo NewInfo = computeInfoForInstr(MI, TSFlags, MRI); 0
981 if (Info.isValid() && !needVSETVLI(MI, NewInfo, Info)) 0
982 return; 0
983 ----
984 const VSETVLIInfo PrevInfo = Info; 0
985 Info = NewInfo; 0
986 ----
987 if (!RISCVII::hasVLOp(TSFlags)) 0
988 return; 0
989 ----
990 // For vmv.s.x and vfmv.s.f, there are only two behaviors, VL = 0 and ----
991 // VL > 0. We can discard the user requested AVL and just use the last ----
992 // one if we can prove it equally zero. This removes a vsetvli entirely ----
993 // if the types match or allows use of cheaper avl preserving variant ----
994 // if VLMAX doesn't change. If VLMAX might change, we couldn't use ----
995 // the 'vsetvli x0, x0, vtype" variant, so we avoid the transform to ----
996 // prevent extending live range of an avl register operand. ----
997 // TODO: We can probably relax this for immediates. ----
998 if (isScalarMoveInstr(MI) && PrevInfo.isValid() && 0
999 PrevInfo.hasEquallyZeroAVL(Info, *MRI) && 0
1000 Info.hasSameVLMAX(PrevInfo)) { 0
1001 if (PrevInfo.hasAVLImm()) 0
1002 Info.setAVLImm(PrevInfo.getAVLImm()); 0
1003 else ----
1004 Info.setAVLReg(PrevInfo.getAVLReg()); 0
1005 return; 0
1006 } ----
1007 ----
1008 // If AVL is defined by a vsetvli with the same VLMAX, we can ----
1009 // replace the AVL operand with the AVL of the defining vsetvli. ----
1010 // We avoid general register AVLs to avoid extending live ranges ----
1011 // without being sure we can kill the original source reg entirely. ----
1012 if (!Info.hasAVLReg() || !Info.getAVLReg().isVirtual()) 0
1013 return; 0
1014 MachineInstr *DefMI = MRI->getVRegDef(Info.getAVLReg()); 0
1015 if (!DefMI || !isVectorConfigInstr(*DefMI)) 0
1016 return; 0
1017 ----
1018 VSETVLIInfo DefInfo = getInfoForVSETVLI(*DefMI); 0
1019 if (DefInfo.hasSameVLMAX(Info) && 0
1020 (DefInfo.hasAVLImm() || DefInfo.getAVLReg() == RISCV::X0)) { 0
1021 if (DefInfo.hasAVLImm()) 0
1022 Info.setAVLImm(DefInfo.getAVLImm()); 0
1023 else ----
1024 Info.setAVLReg(DefInfo.getAVLReg()); 0
1025 return; 0
1026 } ----
1027 } ----
1028 ----
1029 // Given a state with which we evaluated MI (see transferBefore above for why ----
1030 // this might be different that the state MI requested), modify the state to ----
1031 // reflect the changes MI might make. ----
1032 void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::transferAfter(VSETVLIInfo &Info, const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1033 if (isVectorConfigInstr(MI)) { 0
1034 Info = getInfoForVSETVLI(MI); 0
1035 return; 0
1036 } ----
1037 ----
1038 if (RISCV::isFaultFirstLoad(MI)) { 0
1039 // Update AVL to vl-output of the fault first load. ----
1040 Info.setAVLReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1041 return; 0
1042 } ----
1043 ----
1044 // If this is something that updates VL/VTYPE that we don't know about, set ----
1045 // the state to unknown. ----
1046 if (MI.isCall() || MI.isInlineAsm() || MI.modifiesRegister(RISCV::VL) || 0
1047 MI.modifiesRegister(RISCV::VTYPE)) 0
1048 Info = VSETVLIInfo::getUnknown(); 0
1049 } ----
1050 ----
1051 bool RISCVInsertVSETVLI::computeVLVTYPEChanges(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1052 bool HadVectorOp = false; 0
1053 ----
1054 BlockData &BBInfo = BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()]; 0
1055 BBInfo.Change = BBInfo.Pred; 0
1056 for (const MachineInstr &MI : MBB) { 0
1057 transferBefore(BBInfo.Change, MI); 0
1058 ----
1059 if (isVectorConfigInstr(MI) || RISCVII::hasSEWOp(MI.getDesc().TSFlags)) 0
1060 HadVectorOp = true; 0
1061 ----
1062 transferAfter(BBInfo.Change, MI); 0
1063 } ----
1064 ----
1065 return HadVectorOp; 0
1066 } ----
1067 ----
1068 void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::computeIncomingVLVTYPE(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1069 ----
1070 BlockData &BBInfo = BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()]; 0
1071 ----
1072 BBInfo.InQueue = false; 0
1073 ----
1074 // Start with the previous entry so that we keep the most conservative state ----
1075 // we have ever found. ----
1076 VSETVLIInfo InInfo = BBInfo.Pred; 0
1077 if (MBB.pred_empty()) { 0
1078 // There are no predecessors, so use the default starting status. ----
1079 InInfo.setUnknown(); 0
1080 } else { ----
1081 for (MachineBasicBlock *P : MBB.predecessors()) 0
1082 InInfo = InInfo.intersect(BlockInfo[P->getNumber()].Exit); 0
1083 } ----
1084 ----
1085 // If we don't have any valid predecessor value, wait until we do. ----
1086 if (!InInfo.isValid()) 0
1087 return; 0
1088 ----
1089 // If no change, no need to rerun block ----
1090 if (InInfo == BBInfo.Pred) 0
1091 return; 0
1092 ----
1093 BBInfo.Pred = InInfo; 0
1094 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Entry state of " << printMBBReference(MBB) 0
1095 << " changed to " << BBInfo.Pred << "\n"); ----
1096 ----
1097 // Note: It's tempting to cache the state changes here, but due to the ----
1098 // compatibility checks performed a blocks output state can change based on ----
1099 // the input state. To cache, we'd have to add logic for finding ----
1100 // never-compatible state changes. ----
1101 computeVLVTYPEChanges(MBB); 0
1102 VSETVLIInfo TmpStatus = BBInfo.Change; 0
1103 ----
1104 // If the new exit value matches the old exit value, we don't need to revisit ----
1105 // any blocks. ----
1106 if (BBInfo.Exit == TmpStatus) 0
1107 return; 0
1108 ----
1109 BBInfo.Exit = TmpStatus; 0
1110 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Exit state of " << printMBBReference(MBB) 0
1111 << " changed to " << BBInfo.Exit << "\n"); ----
1112 ----
1113 // Add the successors to the work list so we can propagate the changed exit ----
1114 // status. ----
1115 for (MachineBasicBlock *S : MBB.successors()) 0
1116 if (!BlockInfo[S->getNumber()].InQueue) { 0
1117 BlockInfo[S->getNumber()].InQueue = true; 0
1118 WorkList.push(S); 0
1119 } ----
1120 } ----
1121 ----
1122 // If we weren't able to prove a vsetvli was directly unneeded, it might still ----
1123 // be unneeded if the AVL is a phi node where all incoming values are VL ----
1124 // outputs from the last VSETVLI in their respective basic blocks. ----
1125 bool RISCVInsertVSETVLI::needVSETVLIPHI(const VSETVLIInfo &Require, 0
1126 const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) const { ----
1127 if (DisableInsertVSETVLPHIOpt) 0
1128 return true; 0
1129 ----
1130 if (!Require.hasAVLReg()) 0
1131 return true; 0
1132 ----
1133 Register AVLReg = Require.getAVLReg(); 0
1134 if (!AVLReg.isVirtual()) 0
1135 return true; 0
1136 ----
1137 // We need the AVL to be produce by a PHI node in this basic block. ----
1138 MachineInstr *PHI = MRI->getVRegDef(AVLReg); 0
1139 if (!PHI || PHI->getOpcode() != RISCV::PHI || PHI->getParent() != &MBB) 0
1140 return true; 0
1141 ----
1142 for (unsigned PHIOp = 1, NumOps = PHI->getNumOperands(); PHIOp != NumOps; 0
1143 PHIOp += 2) { 0
1144 Register InReg = PHI->getOperand(PHIOp).getReg(); 0
1145 MachineBasicBlock *PBB = PHI->getOperand(PHIOp + 1).getMBB(); 0
1146 const BlockData &PBBInfo = BlockInfo[PBB->getNumber()]; 0
1147 // If the exit from the predecessor has the VTYPE we are looking for ----
1148 // we might be able to avoid a VSETVLI. ----
1149 if (PBBInfo.Exit.isUnknown() || !PBBInfo.Exit.hasSameVTYPE(Require)) 0
1150 return true; 0
1151 ----
1152 // We need the PHI input to the be the output of a VSET(I)VLI. ----
1153 MachineInstr *DefMI = MRI->getVRegDef(InReg); 0
1154 if (!DefMI || !isVectorConfigInstr(*DefMI)) 0
1155 return true; 0
1156 ----
1157 // We found a VSET(I)VLI make sure it matches the output of the ----
1158 // predecessor block. ----
1159 VSETVLIInfo DefInfo = getInfoForVSETVLI(*DefMI); 0
1160 if (!DefInfo.hasSameAVL(PBBInfo.Exit) || 0
1161 !DefInfo.hasSameVTYPE(PBBInfo.Exit)) 0
1162 return true; 0
1163 } ----
1164 ----
1165 // If all the incoming values to the PHI checked out, we don't need ----
1166 // to insert a VSETVLI. ----
1167 return false; 0
1168 } ----
1169 ----
1170 void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::emitVSETVLIs(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1171 VSETVLIInfo CurInfo = BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()].Pred; 0
1172 // Track whether the prefix of the block we've scanned is transparent ----
1173 // (meaning has not yet changed the abstract state). ----
1174 bool PrefixTransparent = true; 0
1175 for (MachineInstr &MI : MBB) { 0
1176 const VSETVLIInfo PrevInfo = CurInfo; 0
1177 transferBefore(CurInfo, MI); 0
1178 ----
1179 // If this is an explicit VSETVLI or VSETIVLI, update our state. ----
1180 if (isVectorConfigInstr(MI)) { 0
1181 // Conservatively, mark the VL and VTYPE as live. ----
1182 assert(MI.getOperand(3).getReg() == RISCV::VL && 0
1183 MI.getOperand(4).getReg() == RISCV::VTYPE && ----
1184 "Unexpected operands where VL and VTYPE should be"); ----
1185 MI.getOperand(3).setIsDead(false); 0
1186 MI.getOperand(4).setIsDead(false); 0
1187 PrefixTransparent = false; 0
1188 } ----
1189 ----
1190 uint64_t TSFlags = MI.getDesc().TSFlags; 0
1191 if (RISCVII::hasSEWOp(TSFlags)) { 0
1192 if (PrevInfo != CurInfo) { 0
1193 // If this is the first implicit state change, and the state change ----
1194 // requested can be proven to produce the same register contents, we ----
1195 // can skip emitting the actual state change and continue as if we ----
1196 // had since we know the GPR result of the implicit state change ----
1197 // wouldn't be used and VL/VTYPE registers are correct. Note that ----
1198 // we *do* need to model the state as if it changed as while the ----
1199 // register contents are unchanged, the abstract model can change. ----
1200 if (!PrefixTransparent || needVSETVLIPHI(CurInfo, MBB)) 0
1201 insertVSETVLI(MBB, MI, CurInfo, PrevInfo); 0
1202 PrefixTransparent = false; 0
1203 } ----
1204 ----
1205 if (RISCVII::hasVLOp(TSFlags)) { 0
1206 MachineOperand &VLOp = MI.getOperand(getVLOpNum(MI)); 0
1207 if (VLOp.isReg()) { 0
1208 // Erase the AVL operand from the instruction. ----
1209 VLOp.setReg(RISCV::NoRegister); 0
1210 VLOp.setIsKill(false); 0
1211 } ----
1212 MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(RISCV::VL, /*isDef*/ false, 0
1213 /*isImp*/ true)); ----
1214 } ----
1215 MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(RISCV::VTYPE, /*isDef*/ false, 0
1216 /*isImp*/ true)); ----
1217 } ----
1218 ----
1219 if (MI.isCall() || MI.isInlineAsm() || MI.modifiesRegister(RISCV::VL) || 0
1220 MI.modifiesRegister(RISCV::VTYPE)) 0
1221 PrefixTransparent = false; 0
1222 ----
1223 transferAfter(CurInfo, MI); 0
1224 } ----
1225 ----
1226 // If we reach the end of the block and our current info doesn't match the ----
1227 // expected info, insert a vsetvli to correct. ----
1228 if (!UseStrictAsserts) { 0
1229 const VSETVLIInfo &ExitInfo = BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()].Exit; 0
1230 if (CurInfo.isValid() && ExitInfo.isValid() && !ExitInfo.isUnknown() && 0
1231 CurInfo != ExitInfo) { 0
1232 // Note there's an implicit assumption here that terminators never use ----
1233 // or modify VL or VTYPE. Also, fallthrough will return end(). ----
1234 auto InsertPt = MBB.getFirstInstrTerminator(); 0
1235 insertVSETVLI(MBB, InsertPt, MBB.findDebugLoc(InsertPt), ExitInfo, 0
1236 CurInfo); ----
1237 CurInfo = ExitInfo; 0
1238 } ----
1239 } ----
1240 ----
1241 if (UseStrictAsserts && CurInfo.isValid()) { 0
1242 const auto &Info = BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()]; 0
1243 if (CurInfo != Info.Exit) { 0
1244 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "in block " << printMBBReference(MBB) << "\n"); 0
1245 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " begin state: " << Info.Pred << "\n"); 0
1246 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " expected end state: " << Info.Exit << "\n"); 0
1247 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " actual end state: " << CurInfo << "\n"); 0
1248 } ----
1249 assert(CurInfo == Info.Exit && 0
1250 "InsertVSETVLI dataflow invariant violated"); ----
1251 } ----
1252 } 0
1253 ----
1254 /// Return true if the VL value configured must be equal to the requested one. ----
1255 static bool hasFixedResult(const VSETVLIInfo &Info, const RISCVSubtarget &ST) { 0
1256 if (!Info.hasAVLImm()) 0
1257 // VLMAX is always the same value. ----
1258 // TODO: Could extend to other registers by looking at the associated vreg ----
1259 // def placement. ----
1260 return RISCV::X0 == Info.getAVLReg(); 0
1261 ----
1262 unsigned AVL = Info.getAVLImm(); 0
1263 unsigned SEW = Info.getSEW(); 0
1264 unsigned AVLInBits = AVL * SEW; 0
1265 ----
1266 unsigned LMul; ----
1267 bool Fractional; ----
1268 std::tie(LMul, Fractional) = RISCVVType::decodeVLMUL(Info.getVLMUL()); 0
1269 ----
1270 if (Fractional) 0
1271 return ST.getRealMinVLen() / LMul >= AVLInBits; 0
1272 return ST.getRealMinVLen() * LMul >= AVLInBits; 0
1273 } ----
1274 ----
1275 /// Perform simple partial redundancy elimination of the VSETVLI instructions ----
1276 /// we're about to insert by looking for cases where we can PRE from the ----
1277 /// beginning of one block to the end of one of its predecessors. Specifically, ----
1278 /// this is geared to catch the common case of a fixed length vsetvl in a single ----
1279 /// block loop when it could execute once in the preheader instead. ----
1280 void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::doPRE(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1281 const MachineFunction &MF = *MBB.getParent(); 0
1282 const RISCVSubtarget &ST = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
1283 ----
1284 if (!BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()].Pred.isUnknown()) 0
1285 return; 0
1286 ----
1287 MachineBasicBlock *UnavailablePred = nullptr; 0
1288 VSETVLIInfo AvailableInfo; 0
1289 for (MachineBasicBlock *P : MBB.predecessors()) { 0
1290 const VSETVLIInfo &PredInfo = BlockInfo[P->getNumber()].Exit; 0
1291 if (PredInfo.isUnknown()) { 0
1292 if (UnavailablePred) 0
1293 return; 0
1294 UnavailablePred = P; 0
1295 } else if (!AvailableInfo.isValid()) { 0
1296 AvailableInfo = PredInfo; 0
1297 } else if (AvailableInfo != PredInfo) { 0
1298 return; 0
1299 } ----
1300 } ----
1301 ----
1302 // Unreachable, single pred, or full redundancy. Note that FRE is handled by ----
1303 // phase 3. ----
1304 if (!UnavailablePred || !AvailableInfo.isValid()) 0
1305 return; 0
1306 ----
1307 // Critical edge - TODO: consider splitting? ----
1308 if (UnavailablePred->succ_size() != 1) 0
1309 return; 0
1310 ----
1311 // If VL can be less than AVL, then we can't reduce the frequency of exec. ----
1312 if (!hasFixedResult(AvailableInfo, ST)) 0
1313 return; 0
1314 ----
1315 // Model the effect of changing the input state of the block MBB to ----
1316 // AvailableInfo. We're looking for two issues here; one legality, ----
1317 // one profitability. ----
1318 // 1) If the block doesn't use some of the fields from VL or VTYPE, we ----
1319 // may hit the end of the block with a different end state. We can ----
1320 // not make this change without reflowing later blocks as well. ----
1321 // 2) If we don't actually remove a transition, inserting a vsetvli ----
1322 // into the predecessor block would be correct, but unprofitable. ----
1323 VSETVLIInfo OldInfo = BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()].Pred; 0
1324 VSETVLIInfo CurInfo = AvailableInfo; 0
1325 int TransitionsRemoved = 0; 0
1326 for (const MachineInstr &MI : MBB) { 0
1327 const VSETVLIInfo LastInfo = CurInfo; 0
1328 const VSETVLIInfo LastOldInfo = OldInfo; 0
1329 transferBefore(CurInfo, MI); 0
1330 transferBefore(OldInfo, MI); 0
1331 if (CurInfo == LastInfo) 0
1332 TransitionsRemoved++; 0
1333 if (LastOldInfo == OldInfo) 0
1334 TransitionsRemoved--; 0
1335 transferAfter(CurInfo, MI); 0
1336 transferAfter(OldInfo, MI); 0
1337 if (CurInfo == OldInfo) 0
1338 // Convergence. All transitions after this must match by construction. ----
1339 break; 0
1340 } ----
1341 if (CurInfo != OldInfo || TransitionsRemoved <= 0) 0
1342 // Issues 1 and 2 above ----
1343 return; 0
1344 ----
1345 // Finally, update both data flow state and insert the actual vsetvli. ----
1346 // Doing both keeps the code in sync with the dataflow results, which ----
1347 // is critical for correctness of phase 3. ----
1348 auto OldExit = BlockInfo[UnavailablePred->getNumber()].Exit; 0
1349 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "PRE VSETVLI from " << MBB.getName() << " to " 0
1350 << UnavailablePred->getName() << " with state " ----
1351 << AvailableInfo << "\n"); ----
1352 BlockInfo[UnavailablePred->getNumber()].Exit = AvailableInfo; 0
1353 BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()].Pred = AvailableInfo; 0
1354 ----
1355 // Note there's an implicit assumption here that terminators never use ----
1356 // or modify VL or VTYPE. Also, fallthrough will return end(). ----
1357 auto InsertPt = UnavailablePred->getFirstInstrTerminator(); 0
1358 insertVSETVLI(*UnavailablePred, InsertPt, 0
1359 UnavailablePred->findDebugLoc(InsertPt), 0
1360 AvailableInfo, OldExit); ----
1361 } ----
1362 ----
1363 static void doUnion(DemandedFields &A, DemandedFields B) { 0
1364 A.VLAny |= B.VLAny; 0
1365 A.VLZeroness |= B.VLZeroness; 0
1366 A.SEW = std::max(A.SEW, B.SEW); 0
1367 A.LMUL |= B.LMUL; 0
1368 A.SEWLMULRatio |= B.SEWLMULRatio; 0
1369 A.TailPolicy |= B.TailPolicy; 0
1370 A.MaskPolicy |= B.MaskPolicy; 0
1371 } 0
1372 ----
1373 static bool isNonZeroAVL(const MachineOperand &MO) { 0
1374 if (MO.isReg()) 0
1375 return RISCV::X0 == MO.getReg(); 0
1376 assert(MO.isImm()); 0
1377 return 0 != MO.getImm(); 0
1378 } ----
1379 ----
1380 // Return true if we can mutate PrevMI to match MI without changing any the ----
1381 // fields which would be observed. ----
1382 static bool canMutatePriorConfig(const MachineInstr &PrevMI, 0
1383 const MachineInstr &MI, ----
1384 const DemandedFields &Used) { ----
1385 // If the VL values aren't equal, return false if either a) the former is ----
1386 // demanded, or b) we can't rewrite the former to be the later for ----
1387 // implementation reasons. ----
1388 if (!isVLPreservingConfig(MI)) { 0
1389 if (Used.VLAny) 0
1390 return false; 0
1391 ----
1392 // TODO: Requires more care in the mutation... ----
1393 if (isVLPreservingConfig(PrevMI)) 0
1394 return false; 0
1395 ----
1396 // We don't bother to handle the equally zero case here as it's largely ----
1397 // uninteresting. ----
1398 if (Used.VLZeroness && 0
1399 (!isNonZeroAVL(MI.getOperand(1)) || 0
1400 !isNonZeroAVL(PrevMI.getOperand(1)))) 0
1401 return false; 0
1402 ----
1403 // TODO: Track whether the register is defined between ----
1404 // PrevMI and MI. ----
1405 if (MI.getOperand(1).isReg() && 0
1406 RISCV::X0 != MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
1407 return false; 0
1408 ----
1409 // TODO: We need to change the result register to allow this rewrite ----
1410 // without the result forming a vl preserving vsetvli which is not ----
1411 // a correct state merge. ----
1412 if (PrevMI.getOperand(0).getReg() == RISCV::X0 && 0
1413 MI.getOperand(1).isReg()) 0
1414 return false; 0
1415 } ----
1416 ----
1417 if (!PrevMI.getOperand(2).isImm() || !MI.getOperand(2).isImm()) 0
1418 return false; 0
1419 ----
1420 auto PriorVType = PrevMI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1421 auto VType = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1422 return areCompatibleVTYPEs(PriorVType, VType, Used); 0
1423 } ----
1424 ----
1425 void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::doLocalPostpass(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1426 MachineInstr *NextMI = nullptr; 0
1427 // We can have arbitrary code in successors, so VL and VTYPE ----
1428 // must be considered demanded. ----
1429 DemandedFields Used; 0
1430 Used.demandVL(); 0
1431 Used.demandVTYPE(); 0
1432 SmallVector ToDelete; 0
1433 for (MachineInstr &MI : make_range(MBB.rbegin(), MBB.rend())) { 0
1434 ----
1435 if (!isVectorConfigInstr(MI)) { 0
1436 doUnion(Used, getDemanded(MI, MRI)); 0
1437 continue; 0
1438 } ----
1439 ----
1440 Register VRegDef = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1441 if (VRegDef != RISCV::X0 && 0
1442 !(VRegDef.isVirtual() && MRI->use_nodbg_empty(VRegDef))) 0
1443 Used.demandVL(); 0
1444 ----
1445 if (NextMI) { 0
1446 if (!Used.usedVL() && !Used.usedVTYPE()) { 0
1447 ToDelete.push_back(&MI); 0
1448 // Leave NextMI unchanged ----
1449 continue; 0
1450 } else if (canMutatePriorConfig(MI, *NextMI, Used)) { 0
1451 if (!isVLPreservingConfig(*NextMI)) { 0
1452 if (NextMI->getOperand(1).isImm()) 0
1453 MI.getOperand(1).ChangeToImmediate(NextMI->getOperand(1).getImm()); 0
1454 else ----
1455 MI.getOperand(1).ChangeToRegister(NextMI->getOperand(1).getReg(), false); 0
1456 MI.setDesc(NextMI->getDesc()); 0
1457 } ----
1458 MI.getOperand(2).setImm(NextMI->getOperand(2).getImm()); 0
1459 // Don't delete a vsetvli if its result might be used. ----
1460 Register NextVRefDef = NextMI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1461 if (NextVRefDef == RISCV::X0 || 0
1462 (NextVRefDef.isVirtual() && MRI->use_nodbg_empty(NextVRefDef))) 0
1463 ToDelete.push_back(NextMI); 0
1464 // fallthrough ----
1465 } ----
1466 } ----
1467 NextMI = &MI; 0
1468 Used = getDemanded(MI, MRI); 0
1469 } ----
1470 ----
1471 for (auto *MI : ToDelete) 0
1472 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1473 } 0
1474 ----
1475 void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::insertReadVL(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1476 for (auto I = MBB.begin(), E = MBB.end(); I != E;) { 0
1477 MachineInstr &MI = *I++; 0
1478 if (RISCV::isFaultFirstLoad(MI)) { 0
1479 Register VLOutput = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1480 if (!MRI->use_nodbg_empty(VLOutput)) 0
1481 BuildMI(MBB, I, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(RISCV::PseudoReadVL), 0
1482 VLOutput); ----
1483 // We don't use the vl output of the VLEFF/VLSEGFF anymore. ----
1484 MI.getOperand(1).setReg(RISCV::X0); 0
1485 } ----
1486 } ----
1487 } 0
1488 ----
1489 bool RISCVInsertVSETVLI::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
1490 // Skip if the vector extension is not enabled. ----
1491 const RISCVSubtarget &ST = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
1492 if (!ST.hasVInstructions()) 0
1493 return false; 0
1494 ----
1495 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Entering InsertVSETVLI for " << MF.getName() << "\n"); 0
1496 ----
1497 TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
1498 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
1499 ----
1500 assert(BlockInfo.empty() && "Expect empty block infos"); 0
1501 BlockInfo.resize(MF.getNumBlockIDs()); 0
1502 ----
1503 bool HaveVectorOp = false; 0
1504 ----
1505 // Phase 1 - determine how VL/VTYPE are affected by the each block. ----
1506 for (const MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) { 0
1507 HaveVectorOp |= computeVLVTYPEChanges(MBB); 0
1508 // Initial exit state is whatever change we found in the block. ----
1509 BlockData &BBInfo = BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()]; 0
1510 BBInfo.Exit = BBInfo.Change; 0
1511 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Initial exit state of " << printMBBReference(MBB) 0
1512 << " is " << BBInfo.Exit << "\n"); ----
1513 ----
1514 } ----
1515 ----
1516 // If we didn't find any instructions that need VSETVLI, we're done. ----
1517 if (!HaveVectorOp) { 0
1518 BlockInfo.clear(); 0
1519 return false; 0
1520 } ----
1521 ----
1522 // Phase 2 - determine the exit VL/VTYPE from each block. We add all ----
1523 // blocks to the list here, but will also add any that need to be revisited ----
1524 // during Phase 2 processing. ----
1525 for (const MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) { 0
1526 WorkList.push(&MBB); 0
1527 BlockInfo[MBB.getNumber()].InQueue = true; 0
1528 } ----
1529 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 0
1530 const MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *WorkList.front(); 0
1531 WorkList.pop(); 0
1532 computeIncomingVLVTYPE(MBB); 0
1533 } ----
1534 ----
1535 // Perform partial redundancy elimination of vsetvli transitions. ----
1536 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) 0
1537 doPRE(MBB); 0
1538 ----
1539 // Phase 3 - add any vsetvli instructions needed in the block. Use the ----
1540 // Phase 2 information to avoid adding vsetvlis before the first vector ----
1541 // instruction in the block if the VL/VTYPE is satisfied by its ----
1542 // predecessors. ----
1543 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) 0
1544 emitVSETVLIs(MBB); 0
1545 ----
1546 // Now that all vsetvlis are explicit, go through and do block local ----
1547 // DSE and peephole based demanded fields based transforms. Note that ----
1548 // this *must* be done outside the main dataflow so long as we allow ----
1549 // any cross block analysis within the dataflow. We can't have both ----
1550 // demanded fields based mutation and non-local analysis in the ----
1551 // dataflow at the same time without introducing inconsistencies. ----
1552 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) 0
1553 doLocalPostpass(MBB); 0
1554 ----
1555 // Once we're fully done rewriting all the instructions, do a final pass ----
1556 // through to check for VSETVLIs which write to an unused destination. ----
1557 // For the non X0, X0 variant, we can replace the destination register ----
1558 // with X0 to reduce register pressure. This is really a generic ----
1559 // optimization which can be applied to any dead def (TODO: generalize). ----
1560 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) { 0
1561 for (MachineInstr &MI : MBB) { 0
1562 if (MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::PseudoVSETVLI || 0
1563 MI.getOpcode() == RISCV::PseudoVSETIVLI) { 0
1564 Register VRegDef = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1565 if (VRegDef != RISCV::X0 && MRI->use_nodbg_empty(VRegDef)) 0
1566 MI.getOperand(0).setReg(RISCV::X0); 0
1567 } ----
1568 } ----
1569 } ----
1570 ----
1571 // Insert PseudoReadVL after VLEFF/VLSEGFF and replace it with the vl output ----
1572 // of VLEFF/VLSEGFF. ----
1573 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) 0
1574 insertReadVL(MBB); 0
1575 ----
1576 BlockInfo.clear(); 0
1577 return HaveVectorOp; 0
1578 } ----
1579 ----
1580 /// Returns an instance of the Insert VSETVLI pass. ----
1581 FunctionPass *llvm::createRISCVInsertVSETVLIPass() { 0
1582 return new RISCVInsertVSETVLI(); 0
1583 } ----
